-- 1. [Problem Restatement] For a rectangle with area 180 ft² and perimeter 54 ft, find the square of its diagonal. 2. [Key Idea] Express the diagonal via a² + b² and eliminate a and b using the relations ab = 180 and a + b = 27 derived from area and perimeter. 3. [Proof] Let the rectangle’s side lengths be a and b (a, b > 0). Area: ab = 180. Perimeter: 2(a + b) = 54 ⇒ a + b = 27. The diagonal d satisfies d² = a² + b². Compute a² + b² from the known sums and products: (a + b)² = a² + b² + 2ab ⇒ a² + b² = (a + b)² − 2ab ⇒ a² + b² = 27² − 2·180 ⇒ a² + b² = 729 − 360 ⇒ a² + b² = 369. Hence d² = 369. 4. [Conclusion] The square of the rectangle’s diagonal is 369.
